# Machine Learning Approach

## Overview

The ML component of this project is designed to move beyond simple threshold-based control toward **predictive and adaptive irrigation** using historical sensor data.

---

## Goal

Train a model that can predict **when to open/close the valve** based on:
- Current soil moisture level
- Temperature and humidity trends
- Time of day / season
- Historical irrigation patterns

---

## Proposed ML Pipeline

```
Sensor Data Collection
        │
        ▼
Data Preprocessing
  - Remove outliers
  - Normalize moisture % (0–100)
  - Feature engineering (rolling averages, time features)
        │
        ▼
Model Training
  - Algorithm: Random Forest / Decision Tree (lightweight, embedded-friendly)
  - Input features: moisture %, temperature, humidity, hour of day
  - Output label: OPEN valve (1) or CLOSE valve (0)
        │
        ▼
Model Deployment
  - Export model to run on Python (Flask server) or ESP32
  - Arduino reads prediction result and triggers relay
```

---

