## Python Libraries (for ML component)

```python
pip install pandas scikit-learn flask joblib
```

| Library | Use |
|---|---|
| `pandas` | Data loading and preprocessing |
| `scikit-learn` | Model training (RandomForestClassifier) |
| `flask` | Serve model predictions as a REST API |
| `joblib` | Save and load trained model |

---

## Flask API (Planned)

```python
# Endpoint: POST /predict
# Body: { "moisture": 28, "temperature": 23, "humidity": 61 }
# Response: { "action": "OPEN" }
```

The Arduino/ESP32 sends sensor readings to this Flask endpoint and acts on the returned prediction.

---

## Current Status

The current implementation uses a **fixed threshold (40%)** for simplicity and reliability in a college lab setting. The ML layer is the planned next step for full deployment in agricultural fields.
